text: Zsa Zsa Gábor (6 February 1917 - 18 December 2016) was a Hungarian-American actress and socialite. Her older sister Magda and younger sister Eva were also actresses and socialites. In 1936 Gábor won the Miss Hungary competition. She was married nine times. In 1986 she married Frédéric Prinz von Anhalt. She had one child, Constance Francesca Hilton. On 18 December 2016, at 6:00 am, Gabor died at the Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center in Los Angeles, California from cardiopulmonary arrest complicated by coronary artery disease, aged 99. Her ashes were buried at the Westwood Memorial Park Cemetery in Beverly Hills, California on 30 December. ==References== ==Other websites== * * *Zsa Zsa Gabor News Category:1917 births Category:2016 deaths Category:Naturalized citizens of the United States Category:Actors from Budapest Category:American movie actors Category:American radio actors Category:American socialites Category:American stage actors Category:American television actors Category:American voice actors Category:Deaths from coronary artery disease Category:Deaths from cardiopulmonary arrest Category:Hungarian movie actors
